      "content": "The `IReactorClient.subscribe(search, callback, view?)` method enables real-time document change listening. It accepts a `SearchFilter` (type, parentId, ids, slugs), a callback receiving `DocumentChangeEvent`, and optional `ViewFilter`. DocumentChangeEvent includes `type` (Created/Deleted/Updated/ParentAdded/ParentRemoved/ChildAdded/ChildRemoved), `documents` array, and optional `context` with parentId/childId. Returns an unsubscribe function. For the internal event bus (via ReactorModule), subscribe to `ReactorEventTypes.JOB_READ_READY` for completed jobs or `SyncEventTypes.SYNC_FAILED` for sync failures. In GraphQL, real-time updates use the `documentChanges` subscription.",
